    "body": "Tested on Cython master 177dbe8 and also 0.27.3 (numpy 1.13.3). CPython 3.6 on Fedora 27.\r\n\r\nHave this example.\r\n\r\n```python\r\nimport cython\r\nimport numpy\r\ncimport numpy\r\n\r\n\r\ndef foo():\r\n    cdef numpy.ndarray[numpy.int8_t, ndim=2] array = numpy.zeros((1, 1), dtype='int8')\r\n\r\n    with cython.boundscheck(False):\r\n        array[0, 0] = 1\r\n```\r\n\r\nCython does not warn:\r\n\r\n```console\r\n$ cython -3 pyxwarn.pyx \r\n\r\n```\r\n\r\nNow add `nogil`:\r\n\r\n```python\r\nimport cython\r\nimport numpy\r\ncimport numpy\r\n\r\n\r\ndef foo():\r\n    cdef numpy.ndarray[numpy.int8_t, ndim=2] array = numpy.zeros((1, 1), dtype='int8')\r\n\r\n    with cython.nogil:\r\n        with cython.boundscheck(False):\r\n            array[0, 0] = 1\r\n```\r\n\r\nNow, a warning emerges:\r\n\r\n```console\r\n$ cython -3 pyxwarn.pyx \r\nwarning: pyxwarn.pyx:11:17: Use boundscheck(False) for faster access\r\n```\r\n\r\nBut **I am** using `boundscheck(False)` for faster access.\r\n\r\ncc @encukou ",
